<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1940-06-17T17:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1940-06-17T17:00:00-05:00" n="972" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d972">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">393.11/2147a: Telegram</note>
                            <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of
                                        State</gloss> to the Ambassador in China</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Johnson</hi></persName>)</head>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1940-06-17T18:00:00-04:00">June 17, 1940—6
                                    p.m.</date></dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>96. Your 265, June 16, noon.<note n="78" xml:id="d972fn78">Not
                                    printed.</note> The Department desires that you communicate to
                                American citizens the information contained in the Japanese
                                notification under reference and that you advise the American <pb facs="0890" n="882" xml:id="pg_882"/> citizens concerned in
                                accordance with the penultimate sentence of paragraph numbered 1 of
                                the Department’s 202, June 14, 7 p.m., to Tokyo (94, June 14, 7
                                p.m., to Chungking<note n="80" xml:id="d972fn80">Latter not
                                    printed.</note>).</p>
                            <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi></signed></closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>